1
00:01:49,060 --> 00:01:54,580
=Eight Hundred=

2
00:02:01,180 --> 00:02:08,340
(Months ago)

3
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:12,340
Chen Hui,

4
00:02:13,170 --> 00:02:15,380
several people have told me before

5
00:02:15,380 --> 00:02:16,340
that this stuff

6
00:02:16,340 --> 00:02:18,220
tastes a bit like plastic.

7
00:02:18,220 --> 00:02:19,850
There won't be any problems, right?

8
00:02:19,850 --> 00:02:21,940
How could it taste like plastic?

9
00:02:21,940 --> 00:02:22,780
I don't know either.

10
00:02:30,820 --> 00:02:32,100
It's the taste of this water.

11
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:33,690
From now on, before we ship out,

12
00:02:33,690 --> 00:02:35,450
wash the goods with clean water first.

13
00:02:35,450 --> 00:02:36,290
Got it.

14
00:02:43,620 --> 00:02:47,420
=Episode 11=
(Happy Birthday)

15
00:02:47,820 --> 00:02:53,390
(Efficient and Pragmatic,
Fair and Honest)

16
00:02:53,410 --> 00:02:54,250
Here.

17
00:02:55,610 --> 00:02:56,690
This isn't right.

18
00:02:56,690 --> 00:02:57,780
What is this?

19
00:02:57,780 --> 00:02:59,020
Even the thickness is different.

20
00:02:59,410 --> 00:03:00,980
I heard there's been a major discovery.

21
00:03:00,980 --> 00:03:02,620
Director Tong, hurry.

22
00:03:03,570 --> 00:03:04,820
Hongbing,

23
00:03:04,820 --> 00:03:06,260
is all of this evidence

24
00:03:06,260 --> 00:03:07,220
you brought back?

25
00:03:07,380 --> 00:03:08,220
Yes.

26
00:03:08,410 --> 00:03:09,540
We found it

27
00:03:09,540 --> 00:03:10,780
in the old coal washing plant.

28
00:03:10,780 --> 00:03:12,340
But we don't know

29
00:03:12,340 --> 00:03:13,380
what this foam

30
00:03:13,380 --> 00:03:14,730
was used for.

31
00:03:14,730 --> 00:03:17,940
How did you track it
to the coal washing plant?

32
00:03:18,450 --> 00:03:19,450
Director Tong,

33
00:03:19,450 --> 00:03:20,290
that day,

34
00:03:21,130 --> 00:03:22,540
when I saw the rainbow glow

35
00:03:22,540 --> 00:03:23,980
on the cough syrup bottle,

36
00:03:23,980 --> 00:03:26,130
I felt like I'd seen it
somewhere before.

37
00:03:26,130 --> 00:03:27,570
Then, I remembered,

38
00:03:27,570 --> 00:03:29,080
it was at the old coal washing plant.

39
00:03:29,690 --> 00:03:31,500
In the past, the old plant

40
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:32,340
always used

41
00:03:32,340 --> 00:03:33,730
polyacrylamide

42
00:03:33,730 --> 00:03:35,450
as a flocculant.

43
00:03:35,450 --> 00:03:36,540
Gao Ying's father

44
00:03:36,540 --> 00:03:38,100
developed a skin disease

45
00:03:38,100 --> 00:03:39,270
from long-term exposure to it.

46
00:03:39,940 --> 00:03:41,940
Later, the plant's technology
was upgraded,

47
00:03:41,940 --> 00:03:43,060
new equipment was brought in,

48
00:03:43,060 --> 00:03:44,850
and that's why the old plant
was abandoned.

49
00:03:45,450 --> 00:03:46,380
I see.

50
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:49,260
Have all the drugs
at the scene been counted?

51
00:03:49,260 --> 00:03:50,730
They have.

52
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:51,940
The quantity is massive.

53
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:52,980
It gave me a shock.

54
00:03:52,980 --> 00:03:53,820
How many?

55
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:55,500
Five hundred bottles.

56
00:03:56,060 --> 00:03:57,060
Five hundred bottles?

57
00:03:57,060 --> 00:03:57,900
So many?

58
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:00,660
Have people been assigned
to stake out the scene?

59
00:04:00,660 --> 00:04:02,890
After the discovery,
I told our big guy to stake it out.

60
00:04:02,890 --> 00:04:04,730
Lin just headed over too,

61
00:04:04,730 --> 00:04:06,010
he should be there by now.

62
00:04:06,010 --> 00:04:07,130
We'll do three shifts a day.

63
00:04:07,130 --> 00:04:08,450
Tomorrow, I'm going to the city

64
00:04:08,450 --> 00:04:09,540
to give a special report

65
00:04:09,540 --> 00:04:11,170
to the municipal PSB leadership
about the situation here.

66
00:04:11,170 --> 00:04:12,010
Director Tong,

67
00:04:12,450 --> 00:04:14,380
this is our only lead right now.

68
00:04:14,380 --> 00:04:15,730
We can only follow this line

69
00:04:15,730 --> 00:04:16,850
and see where it leads.

70
00:04:16,850 --> 00:04:17,810
Indeed.

71
00:04:17,810 --> 00:04:19,250
Director Chen, it's pieced together.

72
00:04:23,220 --> 00:04:24,540
What was this used to hold?

73
00:04:26,850 --> 00:04:28,640
Tomorrow, send everyone
from the station out.

74
00:04:29,370 --> 00:04:30,610
All of us, go and investigate.

75
00:04:30,610 --> 00:04:32,020
We must find out

76
00:04:32,020 --> 00:04:33,370
what this thing

77
00:04:33,370 --> 00:04:34,810
was actually for.

78
00:04:38,540 --> 00:04:41,340
Boss, have you seen
packaging like this in the photo?

79
00:04:41,340 --> 00:04:42,290
Do we have this product

80
00:04:42,290 --> 00:04:43,880
in this type of packaging in our store?

81
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:46,100
Never seen it.

82
00:04:46,100 --> 00:04:47,850
This packaging wouldn't be for medicine.

83
00:04:47,850 --> 00:04:50,140
Go to the electronics shop next door
and ask Wang.

84
00:04:50,140 --> 00:04:50,980
Electronics?

85
00:04:52,050 --> 00:04:53,780
(Xiaojian Home Appliances)
Right? See how the picture looks?

86
00:04:53,780 --> 00:04:55,580
Isn't it much better
than that black-and-white one?

87
00:04:55,580 --> 00:04:56,610
I just got it in.

88
00:04:57,300 --> 00:04:58,140
(High-End Customization)

89
00:04:58,140 --> 00:05:00,660
(Raojiang Radio Company
Welcomes All Customers)

90
00:05:02,410 --> 00:05:03,660
This looks about the same

91
00:05:03,660 --> 00:05:04,500
as this one, right?

92
00:05:05,700 --> 00:05:06,580
This should be

93
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:07,490
an imported VCD player.

94
00:05:08,020 --> 00:05:10,700
They were quite popular
in Jin'gang a couple of years ago.

95
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:12,370
I don't have any in stock now.

96
00:05:12,370 --> 00:05:13,250
Could you give me

97
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:14,220
a copy of this manual?

98
00:05:14,930 --> 00:05:15,770
Sure.

99
00:05:16,540 --> 00:05:17,940
Great, thanks.

100
00:05:17,940 --> 00:05:20,100
(Jiangbin Municipal People's Hospital)

101
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:21,430
Wang Dayu, come in.

102
00:05:22,580 --> 00:05:23,490
Excuse me.

103
00:05:23,490 --> 00:05:24,850
I'm sorry.

104
00:05:24,850 --> 00:05:25,850
Sorry, I didn't hurt you, did I?

105
00:05:25,850 --> 00:05:26,690
No.

106
00:05:33,140 --> 00:05:34,380
(Danshen Injection)

107
00:05:46,060 --> 00:05:46,900
Officer Liu.

108
00:05:48,140 --> 00:05:48,980
Officer Liu.

109
00:05:50,660 --> 00:05:51,500
Songge?

110
00:05:55,340 --> 00:05:56,290
Thank you.

111
00:06:02,490 --> 00:06:03,820
Are you all right, Officer Liu?

112
00:06:05,580 --> 00:06:06,490
I'm fine.

113
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:09,020
Are you here for dialysis?

114
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:11,850
I just finished my session.

115
00:06:13,820 --> 00:06:15,050
I'll stay with you for a while.

116
00:06:15,980 --> 00:06:16,820
All right.

117
00:06:18,290 --> 00:06:19,540
Hui

118
00:06:19,540 --> 00:06:21,140
didn't come with you?

119
00:06:21,140 --> 00:06:22,220
He went back to town today

120
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:23,720
to hand over the roller skating rink.

121
00:06:29,250 --> 00:06:30,220
Officer Liu,

122
00:06:31,490 --> 00:06:33,490
I want to ask you a question.

123
00:06:33,490 --> 00:06:34,330
Go ahead.

124
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:36,370
About what you said last time,

125
00:06:36,370 --> 00:06:38,010
viewing life and death
with indifference...

126
00:06:39,850 --> 00:06:40,980
How did you find

127
00:06:40,980 --> 00:06:42,410
such great courage?

128
00:06:45,220 --> 00:06:46,060
Songge,

129
00:06:47,020 --> 00:06:47,860
let me ask you.

130
00:06:49,290 --> 00:06:50,580
Do you love Hui?

131
00:06:51,410 --> 00:06:52,250
Of course.

132
00:06:52,540 --> 00:06:53,660
To protect him,

133
00:06:55,290 --> 00:06:56,460
would you be afraid of dying?

134
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:58,090
No.

135
00:07:01,290 --> 00:07:02,810
Actually, I'm just like you.

136
00:07:04,980 --> 00:07:07,140
Choosing to face all this alone

137
00:07:09,050 --> 00:07:10,610
is also to protect

138
00:07:10,610 --> 00:07:12,100
the people I love.

139
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:14,220
But you've distanced yourself from them.

140
00:07:14,220 --> 00:07:17,080
When they find out the truth later,
won't they be even more heartbroken?

141
00:07:22,410 --> 00:07:23,290
Perhaps.

142
00:07:25,250 --> 00:07:26,700
Or maybe by then,

143
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,460
they will have already forgotten me.

144
00:07:38,930 --> 00:07:39,770
Officer Liu,

145
00:07:40,330 --> 00:07:41,170
is there anything

146
00:07:41,170 --> 00:07:42,540
I can do for you?

147
00:07:43,050 --> 00:07:43,890
For me?

148
00:07:45,730 --> 00:07:46,980
In my current state,

149
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:49,170
I might also have to face

150
00:07:49,170 --> 00:07:51,140
the same situation as you someday.

151
00:07:53,050 --> 00:07:53,890
I think

152
00:07:55,610 --> 00:07:56,700
we are people

153
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:58,170
who can understand each other.

154
00:08:04,730 --> 00:08:06,490
Now, I just want every day

155
00:08:06,490 --> 00:08:08,610
to be fulfilling

156
00:08:08,610 --> 00:08:09,820
and happy.

157
00:08:10,780 --> 00:08:12,540
To have new experiences every day.

158
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:19,140
I like your open-mindedness.

159
00:08:22,540 --> 00:08:24,130
Only then do I feel

160
00:08:24,140 --> 00:08:25,250
that I'm truly alive.

161
00:08:31,140 --> 00:08:38,500
(Yingxiong Roller Skating Rink)

162
00:08:41,100 --> 00:08:48,210
(Yingxiong Roller Skating Rink)

163
00:08:48,230 --> 00:08:49,130
Rental contract,

164
00:08:49,130 --> 00:08:50,130
business license,

165
00:08:50,130 --> 00:08:51,820
(Party B Signature)
and fire safety permit are all here.

166
00:08:51,820 --> 00:08:53,060
Thank you, Hui.

167
00:08:53,060 --> 00:08:54,670
I'll transfer the final payment
to you tomorrow.

168
00:08:56,940 --> 00:08:57,890
- Dad.
- Mr. Chen.

169
00:08:57,890 --> 00:08:59,010
Hello.

170
00:08:59,010 --> 00:09:01,220
You brat, you didn't even say
you were coming back.

171
00:09:01,220 --> 00:09:02,700
I could've had your mom
cook something nice

172
00:09:02,700 --> 00:09:03,700
and had dinner at home.

173
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:05,850
Dad, I have to go back
as soon as I'm done here.

174
00:09:05,850 --> 00:09:07,650
There's so much to do
for the internet cafe's opening.

175
00:09:07,650 --> 00:09:09,460
Isn't it Mom's birthday tomorrow?

176
00:09:09,460 --> 00:09:10,700
Songge and I will be back then.

177
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,100
Your mother really misses you.

178
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:14,060
- I know.
- Boss, where should I put this?

179
00:09:14,060 --> 00:09:15,890
Just put it here. Be careful.

180
00:09:18,130 --> 00:09:19,610
You're putting a VCD player here?

181
00:09:19,610 --> 00:09:21,890
I plan to make this place
look like a small bar.

182
00:09:21,890 --> 00:09:23,610
People can watch TV or something
when they're free.

183
00:09:23,610 --> 00:09:24,610
This looks like

184
00:09:24,610 --> 00:09:26,340
an imported VCD player.

185
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:28,460
They were quite popular
in Jin'gang a couple of years ago.

186
00:09:28,460 --> 00:09:29,300
But I

187
00:09:29,300 --> 00:09:30,700
don't have any in stock now.

188
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:31,540
Hui,

189
00:09:32,580 --> 00:09:34,300
where did you buy

190
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:35,140
this VCD player?

191
00:09:36,730 --> 00:09:38,100
A friend in Jin'gang gave it to me.

192
00:09:38,770 --> 00:09:40,340
It must have been expensive, right?

193
00:09:40,340 --> 00:09:41,730
It's second-hand.

194
00:09:41,730 --> 00:09:43,730
A JVC 717.

195
00:09:43,730 --> 00:09:46,340
A brand-new one cost over
ten thousand back then.

196
00:09:46,340 --> 00:09:48,010
It's outdated now.

197
00:09:48,010 --> 00:09:48,870
It's not worth much.

198
00:09:48,870 --> 00:09:51,040
In all of Fengyang,
there probably isn't a second one.

199
00:09:55,980 --> 00:09:57,010
You still remember, right?

200
00:09:57,010 --> 00:09:59,220
We both discussed this.

201
00:09:59,220 --> 00:10:01,300
When it's your mother's birthday,

202
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,850
we would give her a VCD player.

203
00:10:02,850 --> 00:10:04,340
You haven't forgotten, have you?

204
00:10:04,340 --> 00:10:05,340
I remember.

205
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:07,610
I think this is pretty good.

206
00:10:07,610 --> 00:10:08,940
Such an expensive item,

207
00:10:08,940 --> 00:10:09,820
and your mother and I

208
00:10:09,820 --> 00:10:11,300
haven't even enjoyed it yet.

209
00:10:12,580 --> 00:10:13,490
It's fine, Hui.

210
00:10:13,490 --> 00:10:15,340
If your parents like it,
just take it with you.

211
00:10:15,340 --> 00:10:16,180
Thank you.

212
00:10:16,370 --> 00:10:17,310
It's nothing, Mr. Chen.

213
00:10:17,330 --> 00:10:18,250
Then, according to our accounts,

214
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:19,460
just give me two thousand less.

215
00:10:19,460 --> 00:10:20,300
Fine.

216
00:10:20,510 --> 00:10:21,610
Where is the packaging box?

217
00:10:21,610 --> 00:10:22,700
Let's pack it up.

218
00:10:23,350 --> 00:10:24,300
It's just a short walk.

219
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:25,610
Why do you need a packaging box?

220
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:28,130
If it's packed nicely,

221
00:10:28,130 --> 00:10:29,700
it'll give your mother a fresh feeling.

222
00:10:29,700 --> 00:10:31,250
Won't she be happy?

223
00:10:31,250 --> 00:10:32,460
It's second-hand, Dad.

224
00:10:32,460 --> 00:10:34,580
Who knows where
the packaging went long ago?

225
00:10:34,580 --> 00:10:36,490
Alright, go look for it. Hurry up.

226
00:10:36,490 --> 00:10:37,420
No need, trust me.

227
00:10:37,420 --> 00:10:38,820
You won't find it.

228
00:10:38,820 --> 00:10:40,580
The junk collector
keeps an eye on me every day.

229
00:10:40,580 --> 00:10:42,220
Plastic bottles,
beer bottles, cardboard boxes...

230
00:10:42,220 --> 00:10:43,420
He collects them every day.

231
00:10:43,420 --> 00:10:44,490
Look at you, Hui.

232
00:10:44,490 --> 00:10:45,820
How about this, Mr. Chen?

233
00:10:45,820 --> 00:10:46,890
I'll help you find an empty box

234
00:10:46,890 --> 00:10:48,420
so it's easier for you
to take home. Okay?

235
00:10:48,420 --> 00:10:49,610
We have empty boxes. I'll go find one.

236
00:10:49,610 --> 00:10:50,700
- Thank you.
- I'm going to look now.

237
00:10:50,700 --> 00:10:51,540
Thank you.

238
00:11:05,380 --> 00:11:07,900
(People's Public Security)

239
00:11:07,980 --> 00:11:09,370
(Evidence Box)

240
00:11:09,370 --> 00:11:11,400
Director Chen,
is this the one you're looking for?

241
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:12,610
This is it.

242
00:11:12,610 --> 00:11:13,890
May I use it for a bit?

243
00:11:13,890 --> 00:11:15,220
Sure.

244
00:11:15,220 --> 00:11:16,100
Just sign here,

245
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:16,980
and you can take it.

246
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:22,740
(Chen Hongbing)

247
00:12:48,010 --> 00:12:49,460
What is it for?

248
00:12:49,460 --> 00:12:51,610
JVC 717.

249
00:12:51,610 --> 00:12:53,940
In all of Fengyang,
there probably isn't a second one.

250
00:13:01,530 --> 00:13:03,530
Hui, hurry up.

251
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:07,720
You sell tube popsicles here too?

252
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:09,300
Thirty yuan?

253
00:13:09,300 --> 00:13:11,130
Mine are only one-fifty each.

254
00:13:15,140 --> 00:13:17,210
This bag is so dirty,
yet you're still carrying it.

255
00:13:18,010 --> 00:13:19,250
Why is there blood on it?

256
00:13:22,130 --> 00:13:23,700
- Dad.
- Why are you here?

257
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:24,540
I came to find you.

258
00:13:25,340 --> 00:13:26,180
Director Chen.

259
00:13:27,850 --> 00:13:28,690
It's me.

260
00:13:33,180 --> 00:13:34,730
(Lu Yuan)
I always feel that these people

261
00:13:34,730 --> 00:13:36,010
are always one step ahead of us.

262
00:13:37,300 --> 00:13:38,580
The day of your accident,

263
00:13:38,580 --> 00:13:39,420
what did Huo Kaiming

264
00:13:40,100 --> 00:13:41,220
say to you?

265
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:59,340
(Fengyang Town Police Station
Manpower Distribution Map)

266
00:14:02,890 --> 00:14:04,890
I just hope

267
00:14:04,890 --> 00:14:06,890
that our family

268
00:14:06,890 --> 00:14:08,300
can be harmonious and happy.

269
00:14:19,850 --> 00:14:20,690
Son,

270
00:14:21,530 --> 00:14:22,490
I have no choice.

271
00:14:22,490 --> 00:14:24,420
I'm a policeman.

272
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:25,490
Do you hate me?

273
00:14:33,130 --> 00:14:34,220
For you,

274
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:36,940
I would do anything.

275
00:14:39,650 --> 00:14:41,370
I want you

276
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:43,340
to be happy

277
00:14:45,130 --> 00:14:46,420
for your whole lives.

278
00:14:55,180 --> 00:14:59,540
(Third Police District)

279
00:15:00,340 --> 00:15:06,900
(Efficient and Pragmatic,
Fair and Honest)

280
00:15:19,130 --> 00:15:20,250
You're here so early.

281
00:15:23,980 --> 00:15:24,940
Director Tong.

282
00:15:27,940 --> 00:15:28,940
What's wrong?

283
00:15:29,610 --> 00:15:31,010
Why do you look so pale?

284
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:35,940
I

285
00:15:38,130 --> 00:15:39,530
didn't go home last night.

286
00:15:41,130 --> 00:15:42,180
You were here

287
00:15:42,180 --> 00:15:43,060
all night?

288
00:15:44,340 --> 00:15:45,820
Why?

289
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:46,660
What happened?

290
00:15:53,750 --> 00:15:54,780
It's the VCD player.

291
00:15:55,530 --> 00:15:56,420
You found it?

292
00:15:57,220 --> 00:15:58,130
Where was it found?

293
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:02,140
At

294
00:16:03,460 --> 00:16:04,890
Hui's roller skating rink.

295
00:16:06,770 --> 00:16:07,610
Director Tong,

296
00:16:09,460 --> 00:16:10,340
this way,

297
00:16:12,130 --> 00:16:14,130
the suspicion against Hui

298
00:16:14,130 --> 00:16:15,580
cannot be ruled out.

299
00:16:16,820 --> 00:16:18,370
Now, I can only

300
00:16:19,730 --> 00:16:20,820
apply for recusal.

301
00:16:22,610 --> 00:16:23,530
Wait a minute.

302
00:16:24,250 --> 00:16:25,530
Even if that foam

303
00:16:26,340 --> 00:16:27,650
belongs to Hui,

304
00:16:28,490 --> 00:16:30,460
it can't be considered
direct evidence, right?

305
00:16:31,820 --> 00:16:33,250
When anyone buys an appliance,

306
00:16:33,250 --> 00:16:35,040
don't they just throw
the plastic wrap away?

307
00:16:35,890 --> 00:16:37,250
Our station's situation

308
00:16:37,250 --> 00:16:38,130
is unique.

309
00:16:38,130 --> 00:16:39,420
You know this.

310
00:16:39,420 --> 00:16:41,300
We're too short-staffed,

311
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:42,920
and the area we cover is so complicated.

312
00:16:43,300 --> 00:16:44,300
Regarding this case,

313
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:45,460
besides you,

314
00:16:45,460 --> 00:16:46,530
I really can't find

315
00:16:46,530 --> 00:16:47,770
the right person to investigate

316
00:16:47,770 --> 00:16:49,370
in such a short time.

317
00:16:53,820 --> 00:16:55,010
Then, find a newcomer.

318
00:16:55,010 --> 00:16:55,850
Hongbing,

319
00:16:56,370 --> 00:16:57,490
find a newcomer?

320
00:16:57,490 --> 00:16:58,420
It's not that easy.

321
00:16:58,420 --> 00:16:59,490
In our Fengyang,

322
00:16:59,490 --> 00:17:01,700
it's only an 800-meter radius area.

323
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:04,090
If they argue in the east,
they'll hear it in the west.

324
00:17:04,090 --> 00:17:05,250
If a new face shows up,

325
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:06,900
everyone in the town will know.

326
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:08,090
How would you investigate?

327
00:17:08,090 --> 00:17:10,140
Director Tong, then what
do you want me to do?

328
00:17:11,250 --> 00:17:12,090
How about this?

329
00:17:12,860 --> 00:17:14,220
Come with me to the city again.

330
00:17:15,140 --> 00:17:16,660
We'll report to the Bureau leadership

331
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:18,090
and see what they think.

332
00:17:18,090 --> 00:17:18,930
Sound good?

333
00:17:19,340 --> 00:17:20,290
It's settled. Let's go.

334
00:17:20,290 --> 00:17:21,140
No.

335
00:17:21,140 --> 00:17:21,980
Director Tong,

336
00:17:22,460 --> 00:17:23,300
I...

337
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:26,900
I have one more request.

338
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:27,740
Go ahead.

339
00:17:31,010 --> 00:17:31,980
This machine,

340
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:35,570
can I take it back?

341
00:17:35,570 --> 00:17:36,410
Why?

342
00:17:39,900 --> 00:17:41,810
Today is Ding Yue's birthday.

343
00:17:43,730 --> 00:17:45,290
I told my son

344
00:17:47,050 --> 00:17:49,010
that this was a gift for his mother.

345
00:17:51,900 --> 00:17:53,460
I'm afraid that when Hui gets back

346
00:17:54,660 --> 00:17:56,330
and doesn't see this thing,

347
00:17:56,330 --> 00:17:57,980
it'll be trouble

348
00:17:58,660 --> 00:17:59,770
if he gets any other ideas.

349
00:18:00,900 --> 00:18:02,220
We'll do as you say.

350
00:18:03,490 --> 00:18:04,330
Thank you.

351
00:18:10,860 --> 00:18:11,700
Hongbing.

352
00:18:12,730 --> 00:18:13,570
Hongbing.

353
00:18:14,940 --> 00:18:17,330
Dude.

354
00:18:17,330 --> 00:18:18,490
Tell me

355
00:18:18,490 --> 00:18:20,250
what I should do.

356
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:31,660
(People's Public Security)

357
00:18:31,660 --> 00:18:32,730
Leaders,

358
00:18:32,730 --> 00:18:35,090
(Jiangbin Public Security)
that's exactly how

359
00:18:35,090 --> 00:18:36,010
everything happened.

360
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:44,220
Mr. Chen Hongbing,
please wait outside for a moment.

361
00:18:49,940 --> 00:18:51,220
(Pinglin West Street)

362
00:18:59,570 --> 00:19:00,530
Mr. Chen Hongbing

363
00:19:00,530 --> 00:19:01,660
is a veteran police officer.

364
00:19:01,660 --> 00:19:03,010
In his 20-plus years of service,

365
00:19:03,010 --> 00:19:04,730
he has always worked very hard.

366
00:19:04,730 --> 00:19:06,050
His ability and achievements

367
00:19:06,050 --> 00:19:08,090
are obvious to everyone.

368
00:19:08,090 --> 00:19:09,940
But in this case,

369
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:11,980
the subject of the investigation involves

370
00:19:11,980 --> 00:19:13,050
his son.

371
00:19:13,050 --> 00:19:14,660
We can't be arbitrary,

372
00:19:14,660 --> 00:19:16,180
nor can we be sentimental.

373
00:19:16,180 --> 00:19:17,490
Therefore, I believe

374
00:19:17,490 --> 00:19:19,090
we need to discuss this further.

375
00:19:20,810 --> 00:19:22,380
We've arrived at the city bus station.

376
00:19:22,380 --> 00:19:24,050
For Fengyang or Ping County,
get off here.

377
00:19:35,980 --> 00:19:39,020
(There is no way out for violations.
Reform through hard work for a new life)

378
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:53,540
Hongbing,

379
00:19:54,290 --> 00:19:55,140
how come you're here?

380
00:19:55,940 --> 00:19:57,090
Why am I here?

381
00:19:57,090 --> 00:19:58,090
Because I missed you.

382
00:19:59,220 --> 00:20:01,010
I should have come to see you sooner.

383
00:20:01,010 --> 00:20:03,570
At the station and at home,
there's just too much going on.

384
00:20:03,570 --> 00:20:04,530
I couldn't get away.

385
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:07,320
I brought you two cartons of cigarettes.

386
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:11,410
What's wrong with you?

387
00:20:12,090 --> 00:20:12,930
Are you sick?

388
00:20:13,220 --> 00:20:15,490
It's nothing. Just when I was out
working a few days ago,

389
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:18,180
I worked up a sweat
and caught a chill in the wind.

390
00:20:18,180 --> 00:20:19,310
I've just got a bit of a cold.

391
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:21,300
Did you take medicine?

392
00:20:21,860 --> 00:20:22,730
I did.

393
00:20:22,730 --> 00:20:23,910
I'll be fine in a couple of days.

394
00:20:25,770 --> 00:20:26,610
Hongbing,

395
00:20:27,570 --> 00:20:29,420
you don't look very well.

396
00:20:29,420 --> 00:20:30,460
Did something happen?

397
00:20:31,730 --> 00:20:32,770
What could happen to me?

398
00:20:33,810 --> 00:20:35,330
Nothing's wrong. I just missed you,

399
00:20:36,050 --> 00:20:36,940
so I came to see you.

400
00:20:38,490 --> 00:20:39,330
Right,

401
00:20:39,700 --> 00:20:41,730
there's a question
I've been wanting to ask you.

402
00:20:43,180 --> 00:20:44,020
Ask away.

403
00:20:45,660 --> 00:20:46,530
Do you hate me?

404
00:20:48,380 --> 00:20:49,490
Why would I hate you?

405
00:20:53,140 --> 00:20:54,330
Why don't you hate me?

406
00:20:55,770 --> 00:20:56,810
Let me put it this way.

407
00:20:57,530 --> 00:20:59,660
I'm the one who made a mistake.

408
00:20:59,660 --> 00:21:00,570
It's not like you

409
00:21:00,570 --> 00:21:01,770
framed me to get me in here.

410
00:21:06,090 --> 00:21:06,940
Tell me.

411
00:21:08,940 --> 00:21:09,940
If one day,

412
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:12,980
I meet a friend,

413
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:14,460
and our relationship

414
00:21:16,140 --> 00:21:17,700
is just like ours,

415
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:19,570
if he does something illegal,

416
00:21:21,050 --> 00:21:21,980
and I arrest him

417
00:21:23,140 --> 00:21:23,980
and process him,

418
00:21:24,530 --> 00:21:26,420
will he think the same way you do?

419
00:21:27,140 --> 00:21:27,980
Will he?

420
00:21:28,730 --> 00:21:30,140
That's hard to say.

421
00:21:31,570 --> 00:21:32,490
First,

422
00:21:33,570 --> 00:21:35,490
he has to be someone
who sees things clearly.

423
00:21:35,490 --> 00:21:37,460
If he's a muddled person,

424
00:21:38,570 --> 00:21:39,980
he'll only hate you even more.

425
00:21:42,980 --> 00:21:44,330
See things clearly...

426
00:21:48,460 --> 00:21:49,300
Dad.

427
00:22:11,140 --> 00:22:13,380
Hongbing.

428
00:22:16,290 --> 00:22:17,220
What is it?

429
00:22:17,220 --> 00:22:18,860
Even though you don't say it,

430
00:22:18,860 --> 00:22:20,050
I know in my heart

431
00:22:20,900 --> 00:22:23,010
that something must have happened.

432
00:22:23,010 --> 00:22:24,490
We grew up together.

433
00:22:24,490 --> 00:22:26,420
I know what kind of person
you are very well.

434
00:22:27,250 --> 00:22:28,980
You're good to your family

435
00:22:28,980 --> 00:22:30,290
and loyal to your friends.

436
00:22:30,290 --> 00:22:32,290
No one would think ill of you.

437
00:22:32,290 --> 00:22:34,490
Take me for example.

438
00:22:34,490 --> 00:22:36,180
My lawyer told me

439
00:22:36,180 --> 00:22:37,810
that if I hadn't turned myself in

440
00:22:37,810 --> 00:22:39,700
and hadn't gone with you
to catch Ma Heping,

441
00:22:40,250 --> 00:22:42,250
I'd be facing
at least seven or eight years.

442
00:22:44,180 --> 00:22:45,050
So, for this,

443
00:22:45,820 --> 00:22:46,980
I should actually thank you.

444
00:23:16,050 --> 00:23:16,890
Grandpa.

445
00:23:17,660 --> 00:23:18,500
Grandpa.

446
00:23:19,390 --> 00:23:20,250
You're back?

447
00:23:20,250 --> 00:23:21,220
I'm back.

448
00:23:21,220 --> 00:23:22,420
- You're back.
- Mom.

449
00:23:22,860 --> 00:23:24,010
Where's Songge?

450
00:23:24,010 --> 00:23:25,290
She's getting dialysis.

451
00:23:25,290 --> 00:23:26,420
The hospital is busy today,

452
00:23:26,420 --> 00:23:27,900
so she'll probably be back quite late.

453
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:30,170
But she didn't forget
to prepare a birthday gift for you.

454
00:23:30,180 --> 00:23:31,700
Let me see what it is.

455
00:23:33,460 --> 00:23:35,420
This has our contact information.

456
00:23:35,420 --> 00:23:37,140
It's even a refrigerator magnet.

457
00:23:37,140 --> 00:23:37,980
Look, Mom.

458
00:23:40,220 --> 00:23:41,570
This way, you can reach us

459
00:23:41,570 --> 00:23:42,620
anytime, anywhere.

460
00:23:42,620 --> 00:23:44,180
This is really convenient.

461
00:23:44,180 --> 00:23:45,770
Songge is so thoughtful.

462
00:23:45,770 --> 00:23:46,900
I'm almost done here.

463
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:47,740
Go wash your hands.

464
00:23:50,460 --> 00:23:52,490
Songge is more than just thoughtful.

465
00:23:52,490 --> 00:23:54,660
The cake is sugar-free.

466
00:23:54,660 --> 00:23:56,090
She spent two days looking for it.

467
00:23:56,090 --> 00:23:57,220
It's because she was worried

468
00:23:57,220 --> 00:23:59,420
that Dad and Grandpa couldn't have sugar.

469
00:23:59,420 --> 00:24:02,050
Songge has been attentive
since she was a child.

470
00:24:02,050 --> 00:24:03,700
When you two live in the city together,

471
00:24:03,700 --> 00:24:04,810
take good care of each other.

472
00:24:04,810 --> 00:24:07,010
If you need anything,
just take it from home.

473
00:24:07,010 --> 00:24:09,220
Mom, if you're worried about us,

474
00:24:09,220 --> 00:24:10,700
just come visit us more often.

475
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:16,140
Now,

476
00:24:16,140 --> 00:24:17,420
I finally understand.

477
00:24:17,420 --> 00:24:18,570
Since ancient times,

478
00:24:18,570 --> 00:24:20,570
parents haven't been able
to control their children's affairs.

479
00:24:20,570 --> 00:24:22,940
As long as you think it's right,
just keep moving forward.

480
00:24:26,050 --> 00:24:26,890
Mom,

481
00:24:27,050 --> 00:24:28,010
don't worry.

482
00:24:28,010 --> 00:24:29,620
We'll make something of ourselves.

483
00:24:32,050 --> 00:24:33,250
Of course, you will.

484
00:24:33,250 --> 00:24:34,290
You're my son, after all.

485
00:24:36,090 --> 00:24:37,140
Get me two plates.

486
00:24:37,140 --> 00:24:37,980
Okay.

487
00:24:42,620 --> 00:24:43,700
Alright, that's about it.

488
00:24:43,700 --> 00:24:45,010
Your dad will be home soon.

489
00:24:45,010 --> 00:24:46,660
Go tell Grandpa it's time to eat.

490
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:48,620
Grandpa?

491
00:24:48,620 --> 00:24:51,530
Grandpa.

492
00:24:51,530 --> 00:24:52,370
Time to eat.

493
00:24:52,980 --> 00:24:53,980
Hearing aid?

494
00:24:54,700 --> 00:24:55,660
I'll go find it for you.

495
00:25:44,010 --> 00:25:44,850
Director Tong,

496
00:25:45,860 --> 00:25:46,700
I'm back.

497
00:25:47,730 --> 00:25:48,700
Just arrived in Fengyang.

498
00:25:50,180 --> 00:25:51,700
It's Ding Yue's birthday today.

499
00:25:52,900 --> 00:25:54,380
Hui is back too.

500
00:25:55,530 --> 00:25:57,330
With everything that's happened lately,

501
00:25:58,660 --> 00:26:00,700
I'm very worried about this kid.

502
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:03,460
So I'm thinking of feeling him out

503
00:26:03,460 --> 00:26:05,460
later while we're eating.

504
00:26:05,460 --> 00:26:06,720
Do you think that's appropriate?

505
00:26:16,570 --> 00:26:17,410
Grandpa,

506
00:26:18,490 --> 00:26:19,330
your hearing aid.

507
00:26:21,700 --> 00:26:22,540
Mom?

508
00:26:23,290 --> 00:26:24,980
Dad didn't set up
the VCD player for you?

509
00:26:25,570 --> 00:26:28,250
Can I ever count on him for anything?

510
00:26:28,250 --> 00:26:30,270
He brought it back
and just left it by the door.

511
00:26:30,280 --> 00:26:33,180
The amplifier and the VCD player
were brought back in two separate trips.

512
00:26:33,180 --> 00:26:35,180
I just stuffed them
under your grandpa's bed.

513
00:26:35,180 --> 00:26:37,330
Since you're home today,
can you help me set it up?

514
00:26:38,050 --> 00:26:38,890
Sure.

515
00:26:39,090 --> 00:26:40,460
Where's the VCD player?

516
00:26:40,460 --> 00:26:41,420
It's not under the bed.

517
00:26:42,220 --> 00:26:43,460
Maybe it's in the storage room?

518
00:26:43,460 --> 00:26:44,300
Go check it out.

519
00:27:12,420 --> 00:27:14,570
Several people have told me before

520
00:27:14,570 --> 00:27:15,620
that this stuff tastes

521
00:27:15,620 --> 00:27:17,490
a bit like plastic.

522
00:27:17,490 --> 00:27:19,180
There won't be any problems, right?

523
00:27:19,180 --> 00:27:20,480
It's just the taste of the water.

524
00:27:21,700 --> 00:27:22,770
Where's the packaging box?

525
00:27:22,770 --> 00:27:24,220
Let's wrap it up.

526
00:27:24,220 --> 00:27:25,420
It's second-hand, Dad.

527
00:27:25,420 --> 00:27:27,250
The packaging is long gone.

528
00:27:30,220 --> 00:27:31,730
Director Tong, you heard

529
00:27:31,730 --> 00:27:32,900
what I said clearly, right?

530
00:27:47,180 --> 00:27:48,620
Where's Hui? Where did he go?

531
00:27:48,620 --> 00:27:49,660
I don't know.

532
00:27:49,660 --> 00:27:51,310
He just said he'd help me
with the VCD player,

533
00:27:51,320 --> 00:27:52,530
then he ran out without a word.

534
00:27:54,420 --> 00:27:56,630
You didn't even change your shoes.
Where are you going?

535
00:27:57,010 --> 00:27:58,660
Hongbing, the food is ready.

536
00:27:58,660 --> 00:27:59,620
Come and eat.

537
00:28:11,460 --> 00:28:12,330
Where are you going?

538
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:13,820
I'll be back in a bit.

539
00:28:34,860 --> 00:28:35,810
Let me make a call.

540
00:28:41,440 --> 00:28:42,290
Big guy,

541
00:28:42,290 --> 00:28:43,530
it's Chen Hongbing.

542
00:28:43,530 --> 00:28:44,700
My phone died.

543
00:28:44,700 --> 00:28:46,460
Listen carefully. Bring a few people

544
00:28:46,460 --> 00:28:47,980
to the washing pool
at the coal washing plant.

545
00:28:47,980 --> 00:28:48,820
Yes, right now.

546
00:28:53,620 --> 00:28:56,980
(Golden Peony)

547
00:29:05,820 --> 00:29:12,700
(Heyi Coal Washing Plant, Fengyang Town)

548
00:29:29,660 --> 00:29:30,940
Dad,

549
00:29:30,940 --> 00:29:32,250
let's not wait anymore.

550
00:29:32,250 --> 00:29:33,180
I'll get you some soup.

551
00:29:53,620 --> 00:29:54,460
Ding Yue,

552
00:29:56,420 --> 00:29:57,260
I...

553
00:29:58,420 --> 00:30:00,110
I want to wish you
a happy birthday first.

554
00:30:01,570 --> 00:30:02,620
Thanks, Dad.

555
00:30:02,620 --> 00:30:03,940
For over 20 years,

556
00:30:05,250 --> 00:30:06,090
this family

557
00:30:07,180 --> 00:30:08,420
only felt like a home

558
00:30:09,980 --> 00:30:11,460
because of you.

559
00:30:12,730 --> 00:30:14,050
In the days ahead,

560
00:30:15,090 --> 00:30:16,290
I'll still have to rely on you.

561
00:30:17,050 --> 00:30:18,570
Don't let this family

562
00:30:18,570 --> 00:30:19,660
fall apart.

563
00:30:23,090 --> 00:30:23,930
Dad,

564
00:30:25,330 --> 00:30:26,250
don't you worry.

565
00:30:31,940 --> 00:30:33,010
Let's eat.

566
00:30:34,250 --> 00:30:35,460
Hurry and drink your soup.

567
00:30:35,460 --> 00:30:36,620
Otherwise, it'll get cold.

568
00:30:36,620 --> 00:30:37,940
Okay.

569
00:30:37,940 --> 00:30:38,780
Good.
